+++Section 1 - Introduction & Setup +++
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
0/ setup git repo
1/ install rancher
2/ install brew (package mgr like apt)
3/ install kubectl k9s
4/ install tmux and vim
5/ start rancher desktop with defaults. Rancher starts a VM on your local with a kubernetes cluster. Uses k3s which is a natural progression coming from rancher. 
> kubctl get pods
should return "no resources found in default namespace"
> kubectl get pods -A will show all pods
> cat ~/.kube/config
> k9s
0 in k9s will show all pods
:q in k9s exits

> cd ~
> vim .bashrc
set up alias for kubectl
add alias k='kubectl'
set up autocomplete
source /etc/bash_completion
source <(kubectl completion bash)
complete -o default -F __start_kubectl k

set up vim for YAML: indentation, highlight trailing whitespace etc
vim .vimrc
